sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client Application
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant OnlineSvc as feast-online Service<br/>80/TCP HTTP or 443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Online as Online Server<br/>6566/TCP HTTP or 6567/TCP HTTPS
    participant Store as Online Store Backend<br/>(Redis 6379 / PostgreSQL 5432 / DynamoDB 443)
    participant OIDC as OIDC Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,Store: Flow 1: Online Feature Retrieval
    Client->>Route: POST /get-online-features<br/>Auth: OIDC/K8s Bearer Token
    Route->>OnlineSvc: TLS ReEncrypt<br/>→ ClusterIP
    OnlineSvc->>Online: Forward to pod<br/>Port 6566/6567
    Online->>OIDC: Validate Bearer Token<br/>JWKS Discovery (HTTPS/443)
    OIDC-->>Online: Token Valid + Claims
    Online->>Store: Fetch feature vectors<br/>Store-specific protocol + auth
    Store-->>Online: Feature data
    Online-->>OnlineSvc: JSON Response
    OnlineSvc-->>Route: Response
    Route-->>Client: Feature vectors (JSON)

    participant CronJob as CronJob Container<br/>(kubectl exec)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant FeastPod as Feast Pod<br/>(via kubectl exec)
    participant Offline as Offline Store<br/>(PostgreSQL/BigQuery/Snowflake)
    participant OnlineWrite as Online Store<br/>(Redis/PostgreSQL/DynamoDB)

    Note over CronJob,OnlineWrite: Flow 2: Feature Materialization (CronJob)
    CronJob->>K8sAPI: kubectl exec<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI->>FeastPod: Exec into container
    FeastPod->>Offline: Read historical features<br/>Store-specific protocol
    Offline-->>FeastPod: Feature data (batch)
    FeastPod->>OnlineWrite: Write materialized features<br/>Store-specific protocol
    OnlineWrite-->>FeastPod: Write confirmation

    participant Operator as Feast Operator
    participant Registry as Registry REST API<br/>6572/TCP HTTP

    Note over Operator,Registry: Flow 3: Operator Reconciliation
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Watch FeatureStore CRs<br/>Auth: SA token, HTTPS/443
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: FeatureStore event
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update Deployments, Services, Routes<br/>Auth: SA token
    Operator->>Registry: GET /api/v1/permissions<br/>Auth: Intra-communication JWT (HMAC-SHA256)
    Registry-->>Operator: Permission definitions
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create RBAC Roles/Bindings<br/>Auth: SA token

    participant NotebookCtrl as Notebook Controller
    participant Notebook as Notebook Pod<br/>(kubeflow.org/v1)

    Note over NotebookCtrl,Notebook: Flow 4: Notebook Integration
    NotebookCtrl->>K8sAPI: Watch Notebooks with<br/>opendatahub.io/feast-integration label
    K8sAPI-->>NotebookCtrl: Notebook created event
    NotebookCtrl->>K8sAPI: Fetch FeatureStore client ConfigMap
    K8sAPI-->>NotebookCtrl: ConfigMap data
    NotebookCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create feast-config ConfigMap<br/>in Notebook namespace
    Note over Notebook: Notebook pod mounts<br/>feast-config ConfigMap
